content:
Validates Kubernetes manifests using kubectl dry-run and kubeval to catch configuration errors before deployment. Checks for syntax errors, API version compatibility, and best practices.

```json
{
  "PostToolUse": [
    {
      "matcher": "Edit|Write",
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "if [[ \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" == *.yaml ]] || [[ \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" == *.yml ]]; then if grep -q 'apiVersion:\\|kind:' \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\"; then echo '☸️ Validating Kubernetes manifest...' && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" && kubeval \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" 2>/dev/null && echo '✅ Kubernetes manifest valid' || echo '⚠️ kubectl validation passed (kubeval not installed)'; fi; fi"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```
